The membership of the commission shall consist of three (3) ex officio members and seventeen (17) members who derive from geographically diverse areas of the state and who represent various heritage interests as follows:
The secretary of the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet, or the secretary's designee to serve ex officio;
The president of Kentucky State University, or the president's designee to serve ex officio;
The director of the Kentucky Heritage Council, or the director's designee to serve ex officio;
Four (4) members from institutions of higher education;
One (1) member from the preservation community;
One (1) member from the arts community; and
Eleven (11) members from the public-at-large.
